{"id":3,"parent_id":0,"book_id":44,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":3,"title":"Lesson 2: “Behold, I Am Jesus Christ, the Savior of the World”","subtitle":"","short_title":"Lesson 2","uri":"/manual/doctrine-and-covenants-and-church-history-class-member-study-guide/lesson-2-behold-i-am-jesus-christ-the-savior-of-the-world","content":[["div",{"id":"head1","uri":"/manual/doctrine-and-covenants-and-church-history-class-member-study-guide/lesson-2-behold-i-am-jesus-christ-the-savior-of-the-world.head1"},[".titleNumber","Lesson",["span.dominant","2"]],["h1","“Behold, I Am Jesus Christ, the Savior of the World”"],[".kicker","Reading assignment: Study the scripture passages listed in the following questions and in the scripture chain for this lesson."]],[".bodyBlock",["div",{"id":"p4","uri":"/manual/doctrine-and-covenants-and-church-history-class-member-study-guide/lesson-2-behold-i-am-jesus-christ-the-savior-of-the-world.p4"},"The Bible, the books of Moses and Abraham in the Pearl of Great Price, and the Book of Mormon are ancient testaments, or witnesses, of Jesus Christ. The Doctrine and Covenants is a testament of Jesus Christ given in this dispensation."],["ul.bullet",["li",["span.label","•"],[".para","Read",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/19.16-19"},"D&C 19:16–19"],". What does this passage teach about the Savior’s suffering for us? Why was Jesus willing to experience such great suffering for us? (See",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/18.10-11"},"D&C 18:10–11"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/19.19,24"},"19:19, 24"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/34.3"},"34:3"],".)"]],["li",["span.label","•"],[".para","Read",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/88.14-18"},"D&C 88:14–18"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/93.33"},"93:33"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/11.42-44"},"Alma 11:42–44"],". What can yo